history.content:
This might be a bit much, depending on a few things:

- CS 61C is just a rough class overall. There's so much content that you go through - your performance is really dependent on the instructor

- CS 170 was also alot for me, although if this algorithmic intuition comes naturally to you - I've heard its not too bad. As someone who doesn't have it come naturally, I busted my ass to do well in this class

- CS 188 I've heard workload isn't bad, but exams are ROUGH. So keep that in mind

children.subject: Agreed with Anon Calc that it could be a little too intense, especially with how heavy 61C is. To add on, EE 130 by itself isn't that heavy of a workload, since there's usually just a short problem set every week and a relatively light final project at the end. However, content-wise it can be a little tricky to wrap your head around certain device physics concepts/equations.

history.content: Is taking CS 61C, CS 170, CS 188, and EE 130 a feasible workload?
history.subject: Feasible Workload?
